ank\": 1.3733149823017357e-11, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 517, \"end\": 525, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Honolulu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.921234649343076e-15, \"text\": \"Honolulu\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Honolulu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Honolulu\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an Olympic swimmer\", \"from\": 477, \"to\": 495}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But his greatest accomplishment may have been introducing surfing to southern California and Australia, says Peter (PT) Townend, executive director ofthe Huntington Beach International Surf Museum in southern California.\", \"from\": 536, \"to\": 756, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 614, \"end\": 624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 0.9999999977039806, \"rank\": 2.295687271760659e-09, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}, {\"begin\": 629, \"end\": 638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999740698516, \"rank\": 1.7244120569260894e-08, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 645, \"end\": 650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Griffin\", \"score\": 0.9985162049554389, \"rank\": 0.001472953049050614, \"text\": \"Peter\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Griffin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Griffin\"}, {\"begin\": 690, \"end\": 706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huntington_Beach,_California\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Huntington Beach\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huntington_Beach,_California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huntington_Beach,_California\"}, {\"begin\": 745, \"end\": 755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 0.9999999977039806, \"rank\": 2.295687271760659e-09, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his greatest accomplishment\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 567}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He was the Sultan of Surf.\\\"\", \"from\": 758, \"to\": 786, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Sultan\", \"from\": 766, \"to\": 776}, {\"ngram\": \"Surf\", \"from\": 780, \"to\": 784}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An exhibit that chronicles Kahanamoku's life and his push to see surfing recognized as an Olympic sport is now on at the museum in what is also known asSurf City USA.\", \"from\": 788, \"to\": 954, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 950, \"end\": 953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999998749445, \"rank\": 7.912122047910018e-11, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An exhibit\", \"from\": 788, \"to\": 798}, {\"ngram\": \"Kahanamoku's life\", \"from\": 815, \"to\": 832}, {\"ngram\": \"his push\", \"from\": 837, \"to\": 845}, {\"ngram\": \"surfing\", \"from\": 853, \"to\": 860}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic sport\", \"from\": 875, \"to\": 891}, {\"ngram\": \"the museum\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 915}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It took 100 years for that to happen and now we have Olympians - surfing, gold-medal Olympians,\\\" adds Townend,the world's first professional surfing championand chief curator of the exhibit.\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 1147, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"100 years\", \"from\": 965, \"to\": 974}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympians - surfing, gold-medal Olympians\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1051}, {\"ngram\": \"Townend\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1066}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's first professional surfing championand chief curator\", \"from\": 1067, \"to\": 1131}, {\"ngram\": \"the exhibit\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1146}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sadly, Kahanamoku died in 1968, decades before surfing would make its Olympic debut at the 2020 Games in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1254, \"end\": 1259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9992930100658235, \"rank\": 0.000686973803177117, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kahanamoku\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1166}, {\"ngram\": \"its Olympic debut\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1232}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2020 Games\", \"from\": 1236, \"to\": 1250}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the achievement remains his legacy, says Townend, an Australian living in Huntington Beach, less than an hour south of Los Angeles.\", \"from\": 1262, \"to\": 1397, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9908447526701886, \"rank\": 0.006791968857184341, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 1340, \"end\": 1356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huntington_Beach,_California\", \"score\": 0.9999999939886948, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Huntington Beach\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huntington_Beach,_California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huntington_Beach,_California\"}, {\"begin\": 1385, \"end\": 1396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999940883, \"rank\": 5.821294765587017e-12, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the achievement\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1281}, {\"ngram\": \"his legacy\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1300}, {\"ngram\": \"Townend\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1314}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"By the time I got to Hawaii - he had died in 1968 - I got to Hawaii in '72.\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1475, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1421, \"end\": 1427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"score\": 0.9999999998030944, \"rank\": 1.9675256181235957e-10, \"text\": \"Hawaii\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\"}, {\"begin\": 1461, \"end\": 1467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"score\": 0.9999999998030944, \"rank\": 1.9675256181235957e-10, \"text\": \"Hawaii\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 1403, \"to\": 1411}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But I was able to surf in the tournament - theDuke Kahanamoku Tournament on ABC Wide World of Sports.\\\"\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1578, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the tournament\", \"from\": 1502, \"to\": 1516}, {\"ngram\": \"theDuke Kahanamoku Tournament\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1548}, {\"ngram\": \"ABC Wide World\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1566}, {\"ngram\": \"Sports\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1576}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Townend spent six months researching Kahanamoku's life to build an exhibit comprised of early surfboards, symbols of California beach culture and media accounts of Kahanamoku demonstrating the sport on both coasts.\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1794, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1697, \"end\": 1707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 0.9999999977039806, \"rank\": 2.295687271760659e-09, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Townend\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1587}, {\"ngram\": \"Kahanamoku's life\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1634}, {\"ngram\": \"an exhibit\", \"from\": 1644, \"to\": 1654}, {\"ngram\": \"early surfboards\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1684}, {\"ngram\": \"symbols\", \"from\": 1686, \"to\": 1693}, {\"ngram\": \"Kahanamoku\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1754}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1778}, {\"ngram\": \"both coasts\", \"from\": 1782, \"to\": 1793}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In one of the most dramatic photos, Kahanamoku is shown standing alone on a surfboard facing an Atlantic City, N.J., beach crowded with onlookers.\", \"from\": 1796, \"to\": 1942, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the most dramatic photos\", \"from\": 1806, \"to\": 1830}, {\"ngram\": \"Kahanamoku\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1842}, {\"ngram\": \"a surfboard\", \"from\": 1870, \"to\": 1881}, {\"ngram\": \"N.J.\", \"from\": 1907, \"to\": 1911}, {\"ngram\": \"onlookers\", \"from\": 1932, \"to\": 1941}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Most people do not even know he surfed in Atlantic City before he surfed in California,\\\" recounts Townend, his voice full of admiration.\", \"from\": 1944, \"to\": 2081, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1987, \"end\": 2000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlantic_City_Race_Course\", \"score\": 0.999982471651411, \"rank\": 1.202295172299309e-05, \"text\": \"Atlantic City\", \"types\": [\"Q1777138\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlantic_City_Race_Course\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlantic_City_Race_Course\"}, {\"begin\": 2021, \"end\": 2031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 0.9999999977039806, \"rank\": 2.295687271760659e-09, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Most people\", \"from\": 1945, \"to\": 1956}, {\"ngram\": \"Townend\", \"from\": 2043, \"to\": 2050}, {\"ngram\": \"his voice\", \"from\": 2052, \"to\": 2061}, {\"ngram\": \"admiration\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2080}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was front page news in the (Atlantic City Evening Union) newspaper.\\\"\", \"from\": 2082, \"to\": 2154, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"front page news\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2105}, {\"ngram\": \"the (Atlantic City Evening Union) newspaper\", \"from\": 2109, \"to\": 2152}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kahanamoku was born in 1890 before Hawaii became the 50th U.S. state and grew up to become a champion swimmer.\", \"from\": 2156, \"to\": 2266, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2191, \"end\": 2197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"score\": 0.9999999998030944, \"rank\": 1.9675256181235957e-10, \"text\": \"Hawaii\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kahanamoku\", \"from\": 2156, \"to\": 2166}, {\"ngram\": \"the 50th U.S. state\", \"from\": 2205, \"to\": 2224}, {\"ngram\": \"a champion swimmer\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2265}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He won five Olympic medals for his kingdom in 1912, 1920 and 1924.\", \"from\": 2267, \"to\": 2333, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"five Olympic medals\", \"from\": 2274, \"to\": 2293}, {\"ngram\": \"his kingdom\", \"from\": 2298, \"to\": 2309}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was after he and another athlete of colour - Native American Jim Thorpe - medalled at the Games in Sweden that Kahanamoku showcased the sport of surfing in Atlantic City.\", \"from\": 2335, \"to\": 2508, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2383, \"end\": 2398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Native_Americans_in_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999935494892042, \"rank\": 6.4505523177899195e-06, \"text\": \"Native American\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Native_Americans_in_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Native_Americans_in_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2437, \"end\": 2443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\", \"score\": 0.9999667404282744, \"rank\": 3.3214781461825565e-05, \"text\": \"Sweden\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\"}, {\"begin\": 2494, \"end\": 2507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlantic_City_Race_Course\", \"score\": 0.999982471651411, \"rank\": 1.202295172299309e-05, \"text\": \"Atlantic City\", \"types\": [\"Q1777138\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlantic_City_Race_Course\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlantic_City_Race_Course\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"another athlete\", \"from\": 2355, \"to\": 2370}, {\"ngram\": \"Jim Thorpe\", \"from\": 2399, \"to\": 2409}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2424, \"to\": 2433}, {\"ngram\": \"Kahanamoku\", \"from\": 2449, \"to\": 2459}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 2470, \"to\": 2479}, {\"ngram\": \"surfing\", \"from\": 2483, \"to\": 2490}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Surfing goes back a long time,\\\" Kahanamoku told Surfer Magazine in 1967, \\\"but I remember when I was about eight years old, I guess, when I started surfing here at Waikiki Beach (in Honolulu).\", \"from\": 2510, \"to\": 2702, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2559, \"end\": 2574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surfer_(magazine)\", \"score\": 0.9873203372353455, \"rank\": 0.01284246575342701, \"text\": \"Surfer Magazine\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surfer_(magazine)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surfer_(magazine)\"}, {\"begin\": 2692, \"end\": 2700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Honolulu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.921234649343076e-15, \"text\": \"Honolulu\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Honolulu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Honolulu\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kahanamoku\", \"from\": 2543, \"to\": 2553}, {\"ngram\": \"Waikiki Beach\", \"from\": 2674, \"to\": 2687}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That was a long time ago.\", \"from\": 2703, \"to\": 2728, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We had nobody to teach us how to ride waves or swim.\", \"from\": 2730, \"to\": 2783, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nobody\", \"from\": 2738, \"to\": 2744}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2754, \"to\": 2756}, {\"ngram\": \"waves\", \"from\": 2769, \"to\": 2774}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a matter of fact, we had to learn by ourselves - especially the surfboarding.\\\"\", \"from\": 2784, \"to\": 2865, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a matter\", \"from\": 2787, \"to\": 2795}, {\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 2799, \"to\": 2803}, {\"ngram\": \"especially the surfboarding\", \"from\": 2836, \"to\": 2863}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of the early surfboards on display at the museum resemble heavy toboggans: thick planks of wood with curled ends.\", \"from\": 2867, \"to\": 2985, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the early surfboards\", \"from\": 2875, \"to\": 2895}, {\"ngram\": \"display\", \"from\": 2899, \"to\": 2906}, {\"ngram\": \"the museum\", \"from\": 2910, \"to\": 2920}, {\"ngram\": \"heavy toboggans\", \"from\": 2930, \"to\": 2945}, {\"ngram\": \"thick planks\", \"from\": 2947, \"to\": 2959}, {\"ngram\": \"wood\", \"from\": 2963, \"to\": 2967}, {\"ngram\": \"curled ends\", \"from\": 2973, \"to\": 2984}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Townend said it would be many generations before lighter and shapelier boards were made of fibreglass with foam cores.\", \"from\": 2986, \"to\": 3104, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Townend\", \"from\": 2986, \"to\": 2993}, {\"ngram\": \"many generations\", \"from\": 3011, \"to\": 3027}, {\"ngram\": \"lighter and shapelier boards\", \"from\": 3035, \"to\": 3063}, {\"ngram\": \"fibreglass\", \"from\": 3077, \"to\": 3087}, {\"ngram\": \"foam cores\", \"from\": 3093, \"to\": 3103}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It did not take long for Hollywood to notice Kahanamoku's prowess in and on the water and cast him in bit parts in movies.\", \"from\": 3106, \"to\": 3228, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3131, \"end\": 3140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999863576, \"rank\": 1.3733149823017357e-11, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kahanamoku's prowess\", \"from\": 3151, \"to\": 3171}, {\"ngram\": \"the water\", \"from\": 3182, \"to\": 3191}, {\"ngram\": \"bit parts\", \"from\": 3208, \"to\": 3217}, {\"ngram\": \"movies\", \"from\": 3221, \"to\": 3227}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was beloved in his native Hawaii where he was voted sheriff of Honolulu a record 13 times and named \\\"Ambassador of Aloha\\\".\", \"from\": 3230, \"to\": 3355, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3259, \"end\": 3265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"score\": 0.9999999998030944, \"rank\": 1.9675256181235957e-10, \"text\": \"Hawaii\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\"}, {\"begin\": 3296, \"end\": 3304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Honolulu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.921234649343076e-15, \"text\": \"Honolulu\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Honolulu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Honolulu\"}, {\"begin\": 3348, \"end\": 3353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aloha\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7062264965142028e-19, \"text\": \"Aloha\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aloha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aloha\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"13 times\", \"from\": 3314, \"to\": 3322}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Ambassador\", \"from\": 3333, \"to\": 3344}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The exhibitDuke's Dream Came True: Surfing's Road to the Olympicsis not the only nod to Kahanamoku in Huntington Beach, an oceanfront community.\", \"from\": 3357, \"to\": 3501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3459, \"end\": 3475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huntington_Beach,_California\", \"score\": 0.9999999939886948, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Huntington Beach\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huntington_Beach,_California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huntington_Beach,_California\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The exhibitDuke's Dream\", \"from\": 3357, \"to\": 3380}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympicsis\", \"from\": 3410, \"to\": 3424}, {\"ngram\": \"not the only nod\", \"from\": 3425, \"to\": 3441}, {\"ngram\": \"Kahanamoku\", \"from\": 3445, \"to\": 3455}, {\"ngram\": \"an oceanfront community\", \"from\": 3477, \"to\": 3500}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is a statue of Duke, a star on a Walk of Fame, and bright banners on lampposts proclaiming: \\\"Duke's Dream Came True\\\".\", \"from\": 3503, \"to\": 3626, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3524, \"end\": 3528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duke_University\", \"score\": 0.9999765329300836, \"rank\": 2.290703001950101e-05, \"text\": \"Duke\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \